"Fact-finding" means a process which includes:
The identification of the major issues in a particular impasse;
The review of the positions of the parties;
A resolution of factual differences by an impartial individual or panel; and
The making of recommendations for settlement of the impasse.

"Public employee" means an employee employed by the public employer, except:
Employees involved directly in the determination of policy;
Supervisory or confidential employees;
Student assistants; and
Faculty.

"Supervisory employee" means a public employee who has the authority to act on behalf of the public employer to:
Hire, transfer, suspend, lay off, recall, promote, discharge, assign, reward, or discipline other employees;
Direct employees responsibly;
Adjust employee grievances; or
Recommend effectively one of the actions set forth in items (i) through (iii) of this paragraph, if:

The constitution or bylaws of an employee organization shall require that the employee organization:
Pledge that the organization will accept members without regard to age, race, sex, religion, marital status, disability, or national origin;
Keep accurate accounts of all income and expenses and prepare an annual financial report;
Keep organization accounts open for inspection by any member of the organization;
Make any loans to officers and agents of the organization only on the same terms and conditions that loans are made available to all other members;
Ensure that periodic elections are by secret ballot and subject to recognized safeguards concerning the equal right of all members to nominate, seek office, and vote;
Ensure that individual members have the right to participate in the affairs of the organization; and
Develop and maintain procedures for disciplinary actions that are fair and equitable.

Public employees have the right to:
Organize;
Form, join, or assist any employee organization;
Bargain collectively through representatives they have chosen;
Engage in other lawful concerted activity for the purpose of collective bargaining; or
Refrain from engaging in the activities listed under this paragraph.
